Images are made of pixels.
In this module, we'll be focusing on what happens $inside$ a pixel.
A lot goes on inside a pixel but in short, there are three essential components:  <br/>
[1] the Magnetization of the spins $(M)$;  <br/>
[2] the main static magnetic field $(B_0)$, and  <br/>
[3] the RF field $(B_1)$.
               <br/><br/>
What happens in the pixel determines the image, so as you flip through the pages, try to make this connection between the physics inside the pixel and the image.
